review_blob: Aroma is of a oatmeal cookie and the taste is a smooth, carbonated, oat taste. Hints of other malt but oat is dominate. A very good oat stout.
Not a bad pilsner. Light and a good balance between sweet and bitter. The flavor only lasts briefly. Its better than most commercial beers.
Aroma of fruit, wood, hint of caramel. Tastes of dried fruit, wheat, fig, oat, and is sweet. I really like this style of beer and its one Im looking for when I go shopping. Very good.
A very smooth porter and not really the most active flavor wise. Has notes of coffee, oat, dark chocolate, dried fruit. Not half bad Id buy it again.
Dark copper with a quick fading tan head. A roasted taste of malt, caramel, nuts. It tastes like other doppelbocks Ive had. Pretty good
UPDATED: OCT 14, 2012
Not really an aroma to this but it has a good malty taste to it. Medium head when poured with an amber color. Not half bad.
I remember drinking this my senior year of High School. It was flavorless and awful. If this is Milwaukees best then I really would hate to see their worst.
I find it hard calling this a beer. Just buy Coors light its a little better though both of these "beers" are just made to get you drunk though I would take cheap vodka over this any day,
No flavor, no aroma, and its only good cold. Only reason I drank this was to get drunk in college. Coming back and trying it again makes me question my early college days...

Color is a pale gold with carbonation. Not much head. Nothing in the nose and the taste is watery with little to no flavor. Not really much different with a lime. Ill drink it if its free but I wouldnt buy another.

Pours almost pitch black with a small brown head. Aroma of oat, raisin, malt, dried fruits, some dark chocolate, small hint of espresso. Tastes of oat with a heavy body and a great finish. An amazing Imperial Stout from the Darkwater series.
Pours amber gold with a small head. Tastes sweet with and good balance of flavors similar to other Oktoberfest beers Ive drank. Not half bad I will buy again.
Nose of hops and bitters with a good balance of hop flavor. Im not a big IPA guy but this one was great. A new go to IPA for me.

Smells very hoppy with a decent head. Tastes like most other IPAs out there also it may have been the bars tap but this IPA left me feeling sick after 20 minutes of drinking it. Not one Im going to again due to the fact there are better IPAs out there.
UPDATED: DEC 10, 2012
UPDATED: SEP 4, 2012
Pours dark with an aroma of chocolate and cherry. Tastes like its name sake but the palette is disappointing. Other than that its not half bad.

Pours almost black with a smell of malt and chocolate. Tastes like a chocolate bar was melted with hints of cherry and malt. Not a bad beer but just one I would only drink after dinner or on top of ice cream.

Taste.....is non-existent. Took three more swigs to try to find it but couldnt. Almost like trying to find Waldo. Pale yellow in color with little head or aroma. Only drinkable if cold otherwise it is bad.
Tastes like its name sake. Pours dark with a quick fading brown head. Smells sweet like cream with a mix of malt. Not a bad stout but I liked the Mokah better. A little bit on the sweet side.
beer_name: Southern Tier Blackwater Series: Creme Brulee Stout

review_blob: Smells instantly of coffee with some dark chocolate. Tastes like coffee, chocolate, malt, some hops, hazelnut, and hints of other flavors. It has a pitch black appearance with brownish head and lacing. After trying this beer I always keep a lookout for this at the store because it was a great Imperial Stout.

Pours almost pitch black with good aroma of roast coffee, malt, and hazelnut. Good lacing and head. Tastes like coffee, toffee, malt, some hops, cream and ends with a coffee/ hop finish. Overall a pretty good stout that I would buy again.

Nose smells similar to old English ales with a hops/ malt/ tea smell. Has a medium sized head and is very smooth with a balance of malt and hops with a hint of herbals (tea maybe) in the taste. Overall a very good beer.
Not a bad beer by any means. Very easy to drink and great on a hot day but not so much if the beer warms up. I would just go for Honkers or any other beer in their line as they have more flavor.
Tastes like most summer beers out there. The color is a murky gold with a lemony/ wheat/ hoppy aroma. Goes down smooth with a crisp finish. A good beer but just not remarkable in any way.
Similar to Kalik as both are pale yellow with little taste. Not bad chilled on a hot day but tastes bad at any other temperature. Has a hint of metallic to the taste that Kalik didnt have.
Not too bad but great on a hot day in the Bahamas. Little taste and head but smooth. Reminded me of Landshark Lager.
I was expecting more taste from this beer. Its smooth but with little honey or flavor. Decent aroma but overall I would not buy it again and instead stick with regular blue moon.
beer_name: Blue Moon Honey Moon Summer Ale

review_blob: Not a bad brown ale but not a great one either. Has a light watered down taste for an ale but not bad for a person whom is new to beers. Pale brown with a small head that fades fast. Decent aroma.
Trying to find the taste but there is little. The little taste has a funky sour aftertaste. Pours pale yellow with little head. One beer I buy if its only on special.

Another college beer that has little taste and is cheap. Comes out as a pale yellow. Tastes watered down.  If only they spent more money toward making a better beer rather than wasting it on advertising campaigns.

Not a bad stout but far from the best. When poured right has a creamy texture and light roasted malt taste. Maybe a little bit of a brunt crust taste. This is one beer I can find at most bars and order if nothing else is good on the drink list.
Another College or money saving beer. Very little flavor with the appearance of urine once poured. No amount of advertising can convince me this "beer" is good.

Has a good aroma of hops, chocolate, espresso, and a little fruitiness. Taste is of dark chocolate and espresso with a slight bitterness. Somewhat chewy but in a good way. Overall a very good porter that I would like to buy again.
After the first taste I wanted to vomit. Who thought this was a good idea to make???
This is a beer? Tastes like bad carbonated water. Tried to find the flavor but there is little to none.
A College beer. The aroma is metallic with a hint of grain. The beer has little to no taste and the little taste is of metal and bad bread. Would never drink this unless youre desperate.
